title: 'agent.ml: emit ToolStart/ToolResult events in turn_stream via on_chunk'
---
Modify execute_tool_calls to accept ~on_chunk param. Emit ToolStart before each tool execution, ToolResult after.

IMPORTANT: execute_tool_calls uses Lwt_list.map_p (parallel execution). Tool events from concurrent tool calls WILL interleave in the SSE stream. This is correct behavior — the client must match events by `id` field (already in the protocol spec).

Steps:
1. Add `~on_chunk:(Provider.stream_event -> unit Lwt.t)` to execute_tool_calls signature
2. Before each tool: `on_chunk (ToolStart {id; name; arguments})`
3. After each tool: `on_chunk (ToolResult {id; name; result; is_error})`
4. Thread on_chunk through turn_stream loop → execute_tool_calls call sites
5. Update session.ml turn_stream signature to include on_chunk (already present but verify threading)
6. Update http_server.ml call sites (turn_stream_stream invocations)

Call sites to update:
- agent.ml: both ToolCalls branches in turn_stream loop
- session.ml: turn_stream wrapper
- http_server.ml: the /chat/stream handler

Acceptance criteria:
- Two simultaneous tool calls produce interleaved ToolStart/ToolResult events (verifiable in logs)
- `make test` passes
- No regressions in existing tool execution behavior